<br>
1. Not all wizards complain about Manaburn.   I think that some wizards were under the illusion that they'd get a 3:1 damage to mana ratio which I must concede is complete crack.<br>
<br>
2.  This borders on broken in PvP scenarios.<br>
Wizard casts mana burn on Victim X.  Loots a phat item.  Group starts the colossal beatdown.   Wizard casts insta-gate to nexus.  Wizard walks away scott-free.<br>
<br>
3.  It doesn't seem to be very good with Bane-encounters but then again Banes would probably be the better way to go with mana/damage ratios involved, especially if you get into the idea of Spell Casting Fury 3 and Spell Casting Fury Mastery 3.    Those dramatically increase a wizard's damage to mana ratio on many casts.   Spell Casting Fury/Mastery seems the better buy than Manaburn.<br>
<br>
4.  This is not about Wizards vs Rogues and it never should have been.  Actually I'm surprised to see this thread at all at a rogue board.   However, I think what it is is this.  Some folks busted ass spending a ton of points to get an ability which largely does not seem worth the points spent.  Is it?  Maybe yes, maybe no  - only time will tell.    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubruke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bruke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/28/01 11:11:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Relax guys</span><hr size=1> *****************************************<br>
