<br>
I don't think people realize that Mana Burn costs 17 points to get (Prerequisite of 3rd Level MC) and does nothing for us except serve to lower our damage output.  By the time I med from 0 to FM I could have delt out 12k EASILY on a full bar of mana.  The ratio is also randomized for some mind boggling reason.  I also think people don't realize that the Necromancer version of this, Lifeburn, does the same thing only it lowers the Necros HP and THEN via an HP bond component in the Lifeburn spell, returns them to full HP.  So a Necro can do around 6k dmg and still be full hp/mana when it's finished...<br>
<br>
There are few situations where I could find this useful and that would be something like Kunark Dragons where they die so fast I can only get one spell off.  The last time I did a Kunark dragon was over 2 months ago though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
A reasonable change would be to have it on a 1.8 dmg / mana ratio based off of your current mana available and then have it consume HALF of your current mana available.  This would do about 7-9k (depending on the Wizard) for half your mana bar.  Still pretty useless, but much better than what it is now. <br>
<br>
We get one good class skill in Luclin (Spell Casting Fury Mastery), it would be nice to have Mana Burn be semi-useful.  I have no problems with it using all my mana, as long as it's a decent ratio and not this random bs.<br>
<br>
Commenting on one other thing fast...<br>
<br>
